<div><a name="_calendar_day_of_week" id="_calendar_day_of_week"></a><h3>4.3.6. Calendar day of week</h3><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_4305d227-e56b-43a7-aa6d-9e2d73f6869c" id="_4305d227-e56b-43a7-aa6d-9e2d73f6869c"></a>The calendar day of week is represented as the following time scale component:</p>
<p class="Sourcecode"><a name="_20c66ea4-9e90-419b-b335-72cd64103ee7" id="_20c66ea4-9e90-419b-b335-72cd64103ee7"></a>[i]["K"]</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_4f95ce8a-7ce8-4b92-b188-b695b444c46c" id="_4f95ce8a-7ce8-4b92-b188-b695b444c46c"></a>Where,</p>

  <p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo3;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst">
    [i] represents the ordinal day number in the calendar week;
valid values of [i] are the integers 1 to 7, representing Monday to Sunday,
in accordance with "The week calendar" specified in <a href="#ISO8601-1">ISO 8601-1:--, Clause 4.2.2</a>.
  </p>

<table class="example" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse"><a name="_5efa7860-edc2-47a0-939a-88ae5e6029b7" id="_5efa7860-edc2-47a0-939a-88ae5e6029b7"></a><tr><td valign="top" class="example_label" style="width:82.8pt;padding:0 0 0 1em;margin-left:0pt">EXAMPLE  1</td><td valign="top" class="example">
